{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"sly-sloth-bay","description":"## Why\nS2 (urge-brook-plume) named a `merge_change_409_guard` event in its plan/design for the review-bot's merge-change path (the guard that treats a Gerrit 409 on a merge-change vote as a benign already-voted/stale-image race, staying fail-closed). The event NAME is referenced but was never actually EMITTED in the code — so the guard path fires with no structured log/metric signal, making the 'stale bot image 409s on merges' condition (root-caused during 8903) invisible to observability.\n\n## What\n- In the review-bot voter/merge path, emit a structured `merge_change_409_guard` event (JSON log line, same shape as the other voter signals: merge_detection/merge_change_review/voter_voted) when the 409-on-merge guard triggers, carrying change_id + revision + http_status.\n- Confirm the observability probe (observability.sh) and/or MERGE_CHANGE_ERROR handling account for it (a guarded 409 is NOT an error — it should be distinguishable from MERGE_CHANGE_ERROR).\n- Add/adjust a test asserting the event is emitted on a simulated 409 on a merge-change vote.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `merge_change_409_guard` event is emitted (structured JSON) when the review-bot hits a 409 casting a vote on a merge change\n- [ ] The event is distinct from MERGE_CHANGE_ERROR (a guarded 409 is benign, not a failure)\n- [ ] A test exercises the 409-on-merge path and asserts the event fires\n- [ ] Documented in infra/runbooks/review-bot-ops.md merge-change ops signals list","id":"5308-585b-169f-4a35","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Emit merge_change_409_guard event on merge-change 409 guard path (S2 follow-up)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783116517217194001,"uuid":"5f6fa5cd-316d-44a4-a4cf-64a935f52ef9"}